The paper proposes a method for improving the accuracy and speed of semantic segmentation using deep learning. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG), which are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of adaptive and difficulty-aware learning, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as end-to-end trainable frameworks, which could relate to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
